First build skia and libmypaint. Follow instructions in 'third_party/'.

Install dependencies (look below).
Build enve in 'build/Release' and 'build/Debug'.

You can use linuxdeployqt to create AppImage.
There is already aPPdir structure prepared for you 'build/AppDir'.
Put 'build/Release/src/app/enve' into '/home/ailuropoda/.enve/build/AppDir/usr/bin'.
Put 'build/Release/src/core/libenvecore*.so*' into '/home/ailuropoda/.enve/build/AppDir/usr/lib'.
Put all libsw*.so and libav*.so files in '/home/ailuropoda/.enve/build/AppDir/usr/lib'.

Dependencies:
Install libsw*-dev and libav*-dev (tested with versions 3.4.6 and 4.1.3)
## Ubuntu 16.04
# sudo add-apt-repository ppa:jonathonf/ffmpeg-4
# sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install libswresample-dev libswscale-dev
sudo apt-get install libavcodec-dev libavformat-dev
sudo apt-get install libavresample-dev

sudo apt-get install libgoogle-perftools-dev

sudo apt-get install libglib2.0-dev

If you try to run QtCreator on Ubuntu 16.04 you may run into:
	qt.qpa.plugin: Could not load the Qt platform plugin "xcb" in ""
				   even though it was found.
To solve the problem:
sudo apt-get install libxkbcommon-x11-dev